<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Bees
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://ioway.nativeweb.org/culture/beeking.htm
">The Bee King and the Snake's Daughters</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ioway Indian story about a bee hero who slew two serpent monsters.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Bee Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0979894085/natilangofthe-20
">The Raccoon and the Bee Tree</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A nice picture book based on a classic American Indian legend as told by 19th-century Dakota author Charles Eastman.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0452276500/natilangofthe-20
">Spirits of the Earth: A Guide to Native American Nature Symbols, Stories, and Ceremonies</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Book by a Karuk elder about the meanings of Indian animal spirits, including a chapter on bees.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0595150179/natilangofthe-20
">Insect Mythology</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Interesting book on the role of bees and other insects in world mythology, including Native North America and Mesoamerica.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/048643494X/natilangofthe-20
">The Sacred Bee in Ancient Times and Folklore</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Anthropology book on bee mythology throughout history, including Mayan and Aztec bee tales.
<BR>



